Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce.

Dice @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch pieces. Trim and thinly slice @Scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Strip @Thyme{¼%ounce} leaves from stems; chop leaves until you have 1 tsp.

> For 4 servings: Chop thyme leaves until you have 2 tsp.

Place potatoes in a #medium pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}. Reserve ½ cup potato cooking liquid, then drain and return potatoes to #pot{}.

Mash with @Sour Cream{2%tablespoon}, @Butter{2%tablespoon}, half the scallion greens, @salt{}, and @pepper{} until smooth and creamy, adding splashes of reserved potato cooking liquid as needed. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

> For 4 servings: Use 4 TBSP butter.

While potatoes cook, toss @Green Beans{6%ounce} on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @Olive Oil{}, @salt{pinch} and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until tender and lightly charred, ~{12-15%minutes}.

While green beans roast, pat @Chicken Cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season generously all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a large drizzle of @Olive Oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

> 4 SERVINGS: Season generously all over with salt and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of @Olive Oil{} in same pan over medium-high heat. Add scallion whites and chopped thyme; cook ~{1%minute}.

Stir in @Chicken Stock Concentrate{1}, @Cherry Jam{2%tablespoon}, and ¼ cup plain water. Bring to a simmer and cook until thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Turn off heat; stir in @Butter{1%tablespoon} until melted. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> 4 SERVINGS: Use 1/3 cup plain water and 2 TBSP butter.

Divide chicken, mashed potatoes, and green beans between plates. Top chicken with sauce. Sprinkle potatoes and chicken with remaining scallion greens and serve.

> TIP: If necessary, rewarm mashed potatoes over low heat with a splash of reserved potato cooking liquid for 1-2 minutes before serving.